%section#wv-sundays
  .shadow
  .container
    .row
      .col-md-12
        %h1 sundays - what to expect
        %p You're really welcome to join us on a Sunday whether you are a church regular or have never been before. Our services start at 10.30am. It is a relaxed and informal atmosphere and anyone is welcome to come along. Our Sunday Services and weekly activities have all moved online due to Coronavirus.
        %p
          You can find our <b>Sunday Livestream</b> on our 
          %a{:href => 'https://www.facebook.com/winchestervineyardchurch/'} Facebook Page. 
          If you are not on Facebook, you can 
          %a{:href => '/live'} click here 
          to watch.
        %p 
          All our previous LiveStreams are on our
          %a{:href => 'https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCrz4VsDe4tuh3A8IhWT7ztA/'} YouTube channel
        %p 
          You can find out about everything going on on our 
          %a{:href => '/keepconnected'} Keep Connected page
        %p 
          And plenty of helpful and inspiring 
          %a{:href => '/resources'} Resources here
        %p 
          Are you new to church? Why not visit our 
          %a{:href => '/welcome'} welcome page
          and please do 
          %a{:href => 'mailto:hello@winvin.org.uk?subject=Hello'} email us 
          if you would like a phonecall from one of our friendly team
        %p
          Want to find out more?
          %a{:href => 'mailto:hello@winvin.org.uk?subject=Hello'} Email us with any queries &raquo;
    .row
      .col-md-4
        %h3 we launch with worship
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/sunday/worship.jpg'}
        %p Connecting with God is central to what we do. A live band leads us for about 25 minutes of sung worship. The words are on the screen and you can join in or just sit back and listen.
      .col-md-4
        %h3 learn together
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/sunday/insight.jpg'}
        %p
          We have a talk based on the Bible and our experience of Jesus. It's not just theory; the talks are relevant to our day to day lives and there are always things to put into practice.
        %p
          %a{:href => '#wv-talks'} Listen to recordings of past talks &raquo;
          %br
          %a{:href => '/yobl'} Year of biblical literacy &raquo;
      .col-md-4
        %h3 and make a response
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/sunday/response.jpg'}
        %p At the end of the talk we reflect on what we have heard and respond. There is the opportunity to choose to follow Jesus or to receive prayer. There is no pressure to participate, but always the chance to respond if you wish.
    .row
      .col-sm-4
        %h3 kids' church
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/sunday/kids-church.jpg'}
        %p During our morning service, we run age-appropriate interactive groups for 0-11s so they can learn about Jesus in a safe and fun environment. Our volunteer welcome team at the door can help your family settle in the right places. You can sign your children into their groups from 10.20am.
      .col-sm-4
        %h3 youth
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/youth.jpg'}
        %p During our morning service, our youth (11-18s) meet after worship in the Youth Café. We play games and eat chocolate, whilst learning what it means to follow Jesus as a teenager today.
      .col-sm-4
        %h3 finding out more
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/sunday/coffee.jpg'}
        %p If it's your first visit we'd love to meet you! You can join some of our team in the connect area to have a coffee and ask any questions.
    .row
      .col-xs-12
        %h3 kids are safe here
        %p
          We value the importance of security and safety and are committed to the safeguarding of all children in our care, with all leaders and helpers fully DBS checked. We encourage all parents, guardians and carers to take a copy of our Safeguarding Policy for their own information. Our Safeguarding Officer can be contacted at
          %a{:href => 'mailto:safeguarding@winvin.org.uk'} safeguarding@winvin.org.uk.


