        .row.collapse#wv-talks-older
          - groups.last.each do |talk|
            = haml :_talk_item, locals: { talk: talk }

%section#wv-compassion
  .shadow
  .container
    .row
      .col-md-12
        %h1 compassion
        %p We live out our faith in Jesus by practically serving the needs of people in our city through our Storehouse, Street Teams and partner initiatives.
    .row
      .col-md-4
        %h3 clothing and equipment
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/what-we-do/store-house.jpg'}
        %p
          The Storehouse provide free good quality children’s clothes and equipment to those in need. We run a voucher system and accept referrals from statutory organisations across the area. Please get in touch if you need our services or want to donate 'as new' goods.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'mailto:hello@winvin.org.uk?subject=Storehouse - clothing and equipment'} Get in touch &raquo;
      .col-md-4
        %h3 food and household
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/what-we-do/store-house-food-and-household.jpg'}
        %p
          The Storehouse reach out to serve those in need by providing simple bags of groceries, household items or essential toiletries. To get involved: "grab a bag, fill a bag, give a bag!" All you need to do is pick up a bag on a Sunday and bring it back full.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/winchester-vineyard-website-assets/uploads/fs-full-list.pdf'} Download a shopping list &raquo;
      .col-md-4
        %h3 seasonal initiatives
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/what-we-do/store-house-seasonal-initiatives.jpg'}
        %p
          The Storehouse run various seasonal initiatives such as our school uniform appeal. At Christmas we collect Shoe Boxes for Operation Christmas Child, run a Toy Fair, give away Christmas hampers, and provide parcels for homeless in Winchester.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'mailto:hello@winvin.org.uk?subject=Storehouse - seasonal initiatives'} Get involved &raquo;
    .row
      .col-md-12
        %p
          We also deliver fresh food fortnightly to people who need it, in partnership with Fare Share, and we run basic cookery courses to help people develop new skills and confidence.
    .row
      .col-md-4
        %h3 further afield
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/what-we-do/store-house-further-afield.jpg'}
        %p
          In the winter The Storehouse send boxes of clothes and toiletries to refugees and displaced people from Syria to help them survive through severe weather and conflict. We also send toys to Ebola orphans and disabled children in Sierra Leone, and clothes to children from our
          %a{:href => 'http://kariskids.org.uk'} Karis Kids
          partners in Uganda.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'mailto:hello@winvin.org.uk?subject=Storehouse - further afield'} Get involved &raquo;
      .col-md-4
        %h3 acts 435
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/what-we-do/acts435.jpg'}
        %p
          Through our Storehouse and agency contacts we identify people with limited income who have specific needs. We post needs on the
          %a{:href => 'http://acts435.org.uk'} Acts435 website
          and donors give money which is then sent to our church so that we can meet the need. If you have a need, please get in touch.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'mailto:hello@winvin.org.uk?subject=Acts 4:35'} Get in touch &raquo;
      .col-md-4
        %h3 street teams
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/what-we-do/street-teams.jpg'}
        %p
          On Saturday nights, a team goes out into Winchester city centre with soup, rolls, tea, coffee, blankets, socks, hats and a listening ear. We help those on the streets by providing for basic needs and giving them someone to talk to. We also support the
          %a{:href => 'http://streetpastors.org/locations/winchester/'} Winchester Street Pastors
          scheme.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'mailto:hello@winvin.org.uk?subject=Street teams'} Get involved &raquo;

%section#wv-healing
  .shadow
  .container.wv-caption
    .row
      .col-md-12
        %h1 healing
        %p When we follow Jesus, our lives begin to change. As we grow in our faith, we may find we need to deal with the effects of the past - either things we've done which we wished we hadn’t, or things we've experienced through circumstances or relationships. God loves us and wants us to be free from the things that hold us back.
        %p Life groups and Sunday morning services are a great place to be prayed for. If we want to go deeper there are a variety of different options which are collectively called Streams of Hope. 
        %p First Stop, SOZO, Recovery, LAM, Mindfulness
        %p
          %a{:href => 'https://www.streamsofhope.org.uk/'} Find out more and Book an Appointment &raquo; 
    .row
      .col-xs-12
        %h2 events
    .row
      - @healing_events.first(3).each do |event|
        = haml :_event, locals: { event: event }

